11/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The government reshuffle will be completed by Tuesday (March 15th), Parliament Speaker Slavica Djukic-Dejanovic told a press conference Thursday. 
Debates on the law on government and ministries started on Tuesday and are expected to last until Monday before a vote on the new cabinet. 
The reshuffle is supported by all parties in the ruling coalition, who have agreed to cuts in the number of their ministers.
In other news, OSCE Parliamentary Assembly President Petros Efthymiou said on Thursday in Belgrade that the Western Balkans have special place in the organisation. 
Efthymiou met Parliament Speaker Slavica Djukic Dejanovic and signed an agreement regarding the 20th summit of the Parliamentary Assembly of the OSCE which Belgrade will host in July. 
(Beta, B92, Tanjug, EMportal, Inews, MIA - 10/03/11)
